# <%= current_page.data.title %>

Azure AD is used to give you and your team-mates access to specific subscriptions in Azure. When your github user has access to a subscription, you will be able to view, create and modify Azure resources for your team.


## Access to a an existing team.

Follow the instructions on the [person onboarding guide](/cloud-native-platform/onboarding/person/#azure-ad-groups).

## Creating a new team

If you are unsure which groups you need to be a part of, ask your teammate to create a pull request to [devops-azure-ad](https://github.com/hmcts/devops-azure-ad/blob/master/users/groups.yml) and get it approved by Platform Operations.

It should look like below


```yaml
groups:
- name: DTS test group // this is the name of the group you want to create

